{"article_id":"SblD66qcFvhkQfvd","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"One week after the landmark Supreme Court ruling on the health care overhaul ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"the 2012 presidential candidates have each carved out a peculiar stance","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"-- with Mitt Romney accepting the ruling 's central argument","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"and President Obama rejecting it .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"The court ruled","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that the individual mandate","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"requiring most Americans to buy health insurance","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"was only constitutional","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"if the fine","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"for not buying insurance","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"was deemed a tax .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"While Republicans disagreed with the ultimate outcome of the case","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"-- that is , the law being upheld --","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Romney ultimately said Wednesday","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"he accepts the high court 's finding","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"that the fine is a `` tax . ''","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"Yet Obama ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"while heralding the court decision as a victory for all Americans ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"has come down definitively against the high court 's rationale for that decision .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Obama campaign spokesman Ben LaBolt made the president 's position clear Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"when he was asked in an interview","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"whether Obama `` disagrees with the Supreme Court decision","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"that says","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"it 's now a tax . ''","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"`` That 's right , ''","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"LaBolt said on CNN .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"`` He said","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"that it 's a penalty . ''","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"Obama aides had earlier said","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"the president still views the fine as a `` penalty , ''","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"but this was the first time","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"an aide said","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"the president actually disagreed with the court 's opinion .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Romney 's campaign ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"which has taken heat in recent days","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"for issuing a string of contradictory remarks on the subject ,","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"quickly seized on LaBolt 's comments .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"`` In a curious development , President Obama apparently disagrees with the Supreme Court ruling","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"upholding his health care law , ''","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Romney campaign spokeswoman Amanda Henneberg said in a statement .","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"`` It 's too bad","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"he does n't also see","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"that ObamaCare is bad policy and bad law . ''","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"She reiterated","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"that Romney would start the process","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"of repealing the law on `` Day One of his presidency . ''","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"The flurry of statements and clarifications from both campaigns has attracted almost as much coverage as the impact of the decision itself .","depth":4},{"id":47,"text":"Republicans have decided to accept the court 's argument","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"that the fine is a tax for obvious reasons","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"-- it allows them to batter the president","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"for allegedly breaking a promise","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"not to raise taxes on the middle class .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Obama 's aides ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"in rejecting the court 's logic ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"are surely wary of precisely that scenario .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Romney , with his latest clarification , made clear","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"that the campaign will continue to wield the tax attack against Obama in the months to come","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"-- as part of its multi-pronged argument against the health care law .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Romney 's comments Wednesday , though , marked the second time in three days","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"that the campaign has attempted to clarify its position .","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"Top campaign adviser Eric Fehrnstrom said Monday","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"the candidate thinks","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"the consequence","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"for not purchasing mandated insurance","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"is a penalty .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"Fehrnstrom said","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that position is the same one","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Romney took on a similar fine under the statewide health-care initiative","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"he instituted as Massachusetts governor .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Hours after Fehrnstrom 's comment , the campaign issued a statement","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Romney considers the fine an `` unconstitutional penalty '' rather than a tax .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Romney on Wednesday changed the campaign position ,","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"saying :","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"`` The majority of the court said","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"it 's a tax ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"therefore it 's a tax . ''","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"If nothing else , the clarifications are providing daily fodder for the presidential rivals .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"After Romney 's interview Wednesday , Obama campaign spokesman Danny Kanner mocked the campaign 's conflicting statements ,","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"and drew renewed attention to the similar mandate fine","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Romney instituted as Massachusetts governor .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"`` Mitt Romney contradicted his own campaign , and himself .","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"First , he threw his top aide Eric Fehrnstrom under the bus","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"by changing his campaign 's position","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"and calling the free rider penalty in the President 's health care law","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"-- which requires those","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"who can afford it to buy insurance --","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"a tax .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Second , he contradicted himself","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"by saying","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"his own Massachusetts mandate was n't a tax","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"-- but , Romney has called the individual mandate","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"he implemented in Massachusetts","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"a tax many times before .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Glad we cleared all that up , ''","depth":3},{"id":95,"text":"he said .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":191,"left":176,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":141,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":128,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":123,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":99,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":97,"right":98,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":105,"right":121,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":105,"left":4,"right":104,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":104,"left":101,"right":103,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":100,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":102,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","n